name: Yellow Enamel Inlay Teardrop Post Earrings
description: Measuring 1" in length, this teardrop-shaped post earrings are inlaid with a rich yellow enamel. The gold metal frame has a very nice patina. In excellent vintage condition. These earrings date to the late 1970s. A great buy! View more photos on Minnie's Mostly Vintage's Facebook Page

name: Napier Bright Red Vintage Beaded Necklace
description:
This fire engine red beaded necklace by Napier would add a touch of cheer to any outfit. 

The necklace is 30" long unlatched, with each 3/8" lucite faceted bead separated by a gold-tone saucer spacer bead. 

An estate find, it's in excellent condition with no visible wear or fading.

name: Napier Bright Yellow or Teal Vintage Beaded Necklace
description:
Bright yellow or blue teal round lucite beads separated by small round spacer beads.  

Each of the 68 red beads measures 1/4" and measures 36 unlatched.  

Signed and in excellent condition.

name: Gorgeous Royal Blue Chevron Glass Bead Earrings
description:
These well crafted, very pretty round blue, red, and white Chevron trade beads are nestled between two silver tiny beads dangling from a silver metal hook.  The beads have four layers and are 1/2" round.  The entire earring is 1 5/8" long. 

Also known as star beads, these gorgeous beads have been made in Venice since the late 1400s.  They are made by layering colored glass over a core cane of glass, and repeating it layer by layer.  Finally polishing them to revel the deep royal blue, white, and maroon.  

Most of the newer beads are produced in India and China but are still made in Venice in extremely limited quantities.  These beads were traded all over the world, but mainly in Africa.
